kindred.network.messages

Enum ClientToServerMessage

  • Object
    • Enum<ClientToServerMessage>
      • kindred.network.messages.ClientToServerMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ClientToServerMessage>

    public enum ClientToServerMessage
extends Enum<ClientToServerMessage>
    Contains an enum number for every type of menu-related message the Client can send to the Server. Can also encode and decode these values to shorten and simplify Client to Server messages.
    Author:
    Kindred Team

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      GAME_ACTION
      Sends an action-related to the game being played.
      HOST
      Tries to host a new room to play on the map specified as argument.
      JOIN
      Tries to join the room whose host's nickname is specified as argument.
      MAPS
      Asks the Server for a list of available maps to play on.
      NICK
      If it has no argument, asks the Server for the Client's nickname; if it has an argument, tries to define it as the Client's new nickname.
      QUIT
      Informs the Server that the Client will close.
      ROOMS
      Asks the Server for a list of available rooms to join.
      UNHOST
      Leaves the room that the Client was previously hosting.

      • NICK

        public static final ClientToServerMessage NICK
        If it has no argument, asks the Server for the Client's nickname; if it has an argument, tries to define it as the Client's new nickname.

      • MAPS

        Asks the Server for a list of available maps to play on.

      • ROOMS

        public static final ClientToServerMessage ROOMS
        Asks the Server for a list of available rooms to join. Each room is made of a hosting Client's nickname and the map name they wish to play on.

      • HOST

        public static final ClientToServerMessage HOST
        Tries to host a new room to play on the map specified as argument.

      • UNHOST

      • JOIN

        Tries to join the room whose host's nickname is specified as argument.

      • QUIT

        Informs the Server that the Client will close.

      • GAME_ACTION

        public static final ClientToServerMessage GAME_ACTION
        Sends an action-related to the game being played. The action is forwarded by the Server to the user's opponent in the game.
